alert.note: Alert for San Luis Obispo County Interior Valleys; Santa Lucia Mountains; Southern Salinas Valley (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 27 at 1:47PM PST until February 27 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Southwest winds 15 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph expected. * WHERE...Santa Lucia Mountains, Southern Salinas Valley and San Luis Obispo County Interior Valleys. * WHEN...Until 10 PM PST this evening. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Accumulating snowfall is possible across the highest elevations this afternoon and this evening and locally treacherous winter weather conditions could develop, but these conditions are not expected to be widespread.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
